Ad Text:

StewartBrown

Building and developing financial models, performing analysis, and presenting findings for clients

Communicating with clients and stakeholders throughout project lifecycles · Supporting project delivery, collaborating closely with senior leadership and clients

Driving the use of AI technologies to improve efficiency in analysis, forecasting, and reporting, embedding automation and intelligence into business processes.

Tertiary qualifications with degree in Accounting, Business Analytics or related

A thorough understanding of database techniques and how to interpret information

5+ years of experience in financial or data analysis, consulting, statistics, or a related field

Advanced Excel, Word, PowerPoint & BI skills

AI and machine learning experience to identify patterns, forecast trends, and support data-driven strategic recommendations.

Exceptional attention to detail and analytical capabilities

Strong written and oral communications skills

Strong organisational skills

Team oriented

An ability to interact with stakeholders to provide timely responses and feedback

A commitment to quality improvement and best practice

Australian citizenship or residency or legal working entitlements within Australia.

Desirable: 

Experience in preparing and reviewing financial and management information for decision making

Experience in Consulting, statistics, or a related field highly regarded

Senior Business Analyst

Brisbane | Contract to 30 June 2026 | Government Program

An opportunity is available for two experienced Senior Business Analysts to join a large, business-critical Systems Continuity program within a Queensland Government environment.

Working as part of a dedicated project team, these roles will provide high-quality business analysis support across systems administration and continuity initiatives, engaging closely with business stakeholders, technical teams, and vendors to ensure robust, well-defined outcomes.

The Role

As a Senior Business Analyst, you will be responsible for end-to-end business analysis activities across complex ICT initiatives, including requirements definition, process mapping, stakeholder engagement, and solution validation.

Key responsibilities include:

Eliciting, analysing, and documenting business, functional, and non-functional requirements

Facilitating workshops and interviews with a diverse range of business stakeholders

Developing process maps, business rules, use cases, and user stories

Reviewing information flows across multiple systems and analysing impacts and dependencies

Working closely with technical teams and vendors to validate and refine requirements

Supporting benefits definition and maintaining traceability throughout the project lifecycle

Assisting with proofs of concept and solution evaluation activities

What We’re Looking For

To be successful in this role, you will bring strong senior-level business analysis capability within complex, multi-stakeholder environments.

Key requirements include:

Demonstrated experience as a Senior Business Analyst, with a Queensland Government environment

Proven ability to gather and document business and functional requirements using structured, formal methodologies

Strong experience documenting use cases, user stories, and requirements for complex ICT systems

Proven capability in business process mapping (BPMN), business rules elicitation, and process re-engineering

Demonstrated experience contributing to systems integration, application design, deployment, and enhancement activities

About Our Client

Our client is a leading, government funded organisation which is going through a large digital transformation. As key part of this evolution is scaling their current data capability to support their reporting, analytics, and emerging AI capability.

Role Purpose

This role will play a hands-on and highly influential role in designing, building, and enhancing the organisation's cloud-based data platform.

You will walk into an established snowflake platform, one fit for current purpose, but one being assessed, evaluated and subsequently redesigned for future use. This position will be key to shaping how the platform evolves to be fit for purposes, working closely with the Head of Data and key business stakeholders. You will be involved in vendor section and then management to enable you to scale a team and get the new platform up and running over the next two years.

This isn't a data architect position, but a senior engineer or team leader looking to step into a managerial role whilst remaining hands on technically. You will have a lot of involvement in scope and solution design, taking the lead in scaling and redesigning the platform.

This role is central to improving data accessibility, delivering high-quality data assets, and enabling analytics and advanced data initiatives across the business.

Due to the nature of the data, this role is only open to Australian Citizens, or those with Permanent residency who are on the path to citizenship.

Key Responsibilities

Data Engineering & Design

- Design and deliver scalable data pipelines and data models using modern cloud technologies.

- Build and maintain the organisation's data engineering layer within Snowflake and Azure.

- Develop robust ELT/ETL patterns across batch, CDC, event-driven, and API-based integrations.

Data Platform Delivery

- Oversee platform reliability, monitoring, optimisation, and lifecycle management.

- Ensure data assets are secure, trusted, and well-governed.

Vendor & Partner Management

- Work closely with external vendors and MSPs to ensure high-quality engineering outcomes.

- Provide guidance, technical direction, and quality oversight across delivery partners.

Analytics Enablement

- Provide strong data foundations to support business intelligence, analytics, and emerging ML/GenAI initiatives.

- Translate stakeholder needs into fit-for-purpose technical designs.

Capability Building

- Establish and document best-practice engineering standards and patterns.

- Play a key role in shaping and contributing to a future data engineering team.

Essential Knowledge, Skills, and Experience

- Hands-on technical experience with Snowflake, databricks, dbt, Python, and Tableau.

- Strong ability to design scalable data models and pipelines (without needing to be an enterprise architect).

- Practical knowledge of Azure data services and cloud-native engineering patterns.

- Experience working with ingestion methods including APIs, CDC, batch, and event-driven architectures.

- Familiarity with BI tools and semantic layers (Tableau or Power BI).

- Understanding of governance and metadata tools such as Microsoft Purview.

- Demonstrated vendor management and external delivery oversight experience.

- Excellent communication skills with the ability to simplify complex concepts.

- Experience working within agile, cloud-based engineering environments.

- Relevant tertiary qualifications or equivalent experience.

What's on Offer

- A highly influential role as a key hire within the expanding data function.

- Ownership of a modern, cloud-native data platform and engineering stack.

- Opportunity to contribute to the design and formation of a future data engineering team.

- Exposure to advanced analytics, ML, and AI initiatives.

- Flexible working arrangements (Sydney based).

- $170,000 - $190,000 inc super plus benefits

The Opportunity

As a Strategy Manager, you will join Ramsay Health Care’s expanding Group Health & Strategy Team and play an integral role in delivering the Ramsay 2030 Strategy. Working closely with the Group Strategy Team, the Group Chief Health & Strategy Officer, and senior leaders across Australia and the broader Ramsay Group, you will help shape and implement strategic initiatives that support Ramsay’s next phase of growth. The role offers broad exposure across strategy, operational performance, and high-impact projects, with opportunities to contribute both locally and across Ramsay’s international operations.

What You Will Bring

You bring strong analytical and commercial capability, with the ability to work through ambiguity and complexity in fast-paced environments. You take a hypothesis-driven approach, leveraging data and insight to develop clear, well-structured strategic recommendations that support confident decision-making.

Key Accountabilities:

Lead and deliver strategic workstreams aligned to the Ramsay 2030 Strategy.
Support effective decision-making by driving operational rhythm, cadence, and cross-functional alignment.
Identify, scope, and deliver high-impact strategic projects, including M&A, partnerships, and transformation initiatives.
Develop clear, data-driven insights through analysis, modelling, and storytelling for senior leaders and executives.
Prepare business cases, cost-benefit models, KPIs, and performance reporting to support strategic priorities.
Partner with leaders across Strategy, Operations, and Corporate teams to embed strategy into day-to-day business execution.

Skills & Education

3–5 years’ experience in strategy, management consulting, corporate development, healthcare operations, investment banking, or a similar analytical environment.
Strong problem-solving and quantitative skills, with the ability to work confidently in ambiguous or fast-changing contexts.
Excellent written and verbal communication skills, including the ability to prepare high-quality executive presentations.
Advanced capability in PowerPoint and Excel, with experience in business case development, KPI tracking, and market analysis.
Tertiary qualification in Data Science, Finance, Accounting, Engineering, Economics, Management, or a related discipline (preferred).
Healthcare and/or transformation experience (desirable).
Experience with analytics and data tools such as Google Cloud Platform (BigQuery), TM1, SQL, VBA, Python, or R (desirable).

Benefits

An attractive remuneration package, supported by a comprehensive range of benefits that recognise your contribution and promote your wellbeing.
Opportunities for leadership and professional development, with clear pathways for career growth across Australia’s largest private healthcare provider.
Access to an exclusive rewards program offering premium discounts and privileges with leading national and global brands.
The chance to join a purpose-driven organisation at a pivotal time, where you can contribute to meaningful transformation and help shape the future of high-quality healthcare across the Ramsay network.

About Ramsay Health Care

Founded in Australia in 1964, Ramsay Health Care is the nation’s largest private hospital operator and a global healthcare leader. In Australia, Ramsay operates 76 hospitals and 12 surgical centres, caring for more than 1.1 million patients each year across acute care, complex surgery, mental health, and rehabilitation, alongside public hospitals, clinics, telehealth-supported psychology services, and community pharmacies. With around 35,000 employees and partnerships with more than 9,000 doctors, Ramsay is recognised for strong clinical governance, high-acuity care, and leadership in clinical trials. Guided by its ethos People Caring for People and The Ramsay Way, Ramsay holds around 25% of Australia’s private health insurance market and remains a trusted provider of high-quality, sustainable healthcare nationwide.

To Apply

All applications should include your CV outlining your experience and skills in line with the above. Applications close Wednesday 11th February 2026. Ramsay Health Care is committed to Child Safety. Details of our commitment are set out in our Code of Conduct, available at www.ramsayhealth.com

About Us

With a focus on innovation and delivering better customer outcomes, there has never been a better time to work in the Tasmanian energy sector with Aurora Energy. Be a part of Tasmania’s energy future and make a strong contribution to the ongoing success of our business. 

We work hard to create a workplace that is welcoming and flexible, while balancing the needs of our people, the business and our customers. Our ‘Better Fit’ Program offers hybrid working after a training and/or probationary period to support work-life balance. 

Aurora Energy will invest in you with training and education, celebrate your successes through recognition and reward, and provide a range of employee benefits including an electricity discount, generous leave benefits, and support for your health and wellbeing.  

We believe that every employee has a role to play in contributing to a positive and supportive workplace culture. Our Aurora Way values have been created by our people, for our people. As an employee, you’ll use these values every day to guide your behaviours and actions. Together we’ll continue to make Aurora Energy a great place to work.  

This role sits within our Digital Transformation and Operations Business Unit. They are at the forefront of developing and rolling out new technologies, partnering with the business to solve complex problems, keeping Aurora Energy’s data and systems secure, and much more.   

They collaborate with stakeholders across Aurora Energy to understand problems and identify the best way forward. They take a team-based, people-centric approach. In their words: “There are lots of exciting things to do to support Aurora Energy’s digital transformation, and this breadth is what keeps it interesting.”  

Digital Transformation and Operations is made up of three parts. The Senior Data Engineer sits within Digital Operations.

Digital Operations is made up of an Infrastructure Team, Tech Contracts, Cyber Security, and Service Delivery. Collectively they make sure that all the technology we use in the business, including our systems and reports, is functional and well maintained. They also provide hands-on support for our in-house projects. They are known for being early adopters and champions of new technologies including GenAI.    

About the Role

As our Senior Data Engineer, you’ll lead a talented team and play a hands‑on role in building data solutions that support smarter decisions, better customer experiences and Aurora Energy’s digital future.

You’ll work closely with teams across the business to design, deliver and continuously improve our data and analytics platforms – while championing innovation, quality and good data governance.

In this role, you’ll:

Lead and mentor a team of data engineers.
Design and deliver scalable data and analytics solutions aligned to business goals.
Act as the go‑to expert for complex data engineering challenges.
Drive continuous improvement across our data platforms, tools and ways of working.
Champion agile and DevOps practices, collaboration and learning.
Partner with stakeholders, delivery teams and vendors to get outcomes across the line.

About You

You’re a technically strong leader who enjoys solving problems and helping others succeed. You’re comfortable balancing hands‑on delivery with strategy, and you’re curious about how data can create real value.

You’ll bring:

A degree in computer science or a related field, or equivalent experience.
Strong experience in data engineering, analytics and business intelligence, including cloud platforms.
Experience leading or coaching engineers or analysts.
Solid problem‑solving and solution‑design skills.
Confidence working with stakeholders in a fast‑moving environment.
Experience working in agile teams and a passion for continuous improvement.

Experience with Snowflake, cloud‑based data transformation tools or data governance frameworks is a plus. At least two years’ experience in a similar role is desirable.  

What’s on Offer

With a focus on innovation and delivering better customer outcomes, there has never been a better time to work in the Tasmanian energy sector with Aurora Energy. Be a part of Tasmanians’ energy future and make a strong contribution to the ongoing success of our business.

We work hard to create a workplace that is welcoming and flexible, while balancing the needs of our people, the business and our customers.

Our ‘Better Fit’ Program offers hybrid working after a training and/or probationary period. Our offices feature collaborative spaces, quiet pods, sit/stand desks, and meetings rooms of all sizes—all fully integrated with the latest collaborative working technologies and amenities.

How to Apply

If you have what it takes, please click ‘I’m interested’ or 'apply', ensuring you attach a cover letter outlining how your skills and experience are aligned with this role, as well as an up-to-date resume. Applications without a cover letter will not be considered.

You will be required to satisfy a National Criminal History Police Check. 

Applications close 9am Wednesday, 25 February 2026.

Job Title: Senior Business Analyst – Private Health Insurance (PHI)
Ad Text:
Role Overview

We are seeking a Senior Business Analyst with strong Australian Private Health Insurance (PHI) experience, particularly across memberships, products, premiums, and claims. This role supports business and technology initiatives within a health fund environment and requires a practical understanding of how PHI operations translate into system behaviour and data outcomes.

The successful candidate will be comfortable working across core PHI processes and supporting integrations with Medicare, HICAPS, and ECLIPSE, while collaborating closely with business SMEs and delivery teams.


Key Responsibilities
• Lead business analysis activities across PHI initiatives impacting membership management, product configuration, premium billing, and claims processing
• Work with business stakeholders to capture and document requirements related to:
• Member lifecycle events (joins, transfers, suspensions, terminations)
• Product and cover structures (Hospital, Extras, combined covers)
• Premium calculation, payment frequency, arrears, and advance payments
• Claims submission, assessment, and benefit calculation
• Analyse and document as-is and to-be processes, business rules, and system interactions
• Support initiatives involving external PHI interfaces, including:
• HICAPS (electronic and POS claiming)
• ECLIPSE (hospital and medical claiming)
• Medicare coordination and related interactions
• Translate business requirements into clear functional specifications and user stories
• Collaborate with solution designers, developers, and testers to ensure requirements are correctly implemented
• Support SIT and UAT by defining PHI-relevant test scenarios and validating outcomes against expected business rules
• Assist with implementation activities, change impacts, and post-release support

Mandatory Skills & Experience:


• Proven experience as a Senior Business Analyst within the Australian PHI domain
• Strong understanding of core PHI operations, including:
• Membership and policy administration
• Product and benefit structures
• Premiums, payments, and billing cycles
• Claims processing and benefit calculation
• Experience supporting or analysing PHI integrations such as HICAPS, ECLIPSE, and Medicare
• Ability to interpret fund rules and translate them into system and data requirements
• Strong documentation skills (business requirements, functional specs, process flows, user stories)
• Experience working in Agile, Waterfall, or hybrid delivery environments
• Strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills


Desirable Experience
• Experience working with PHI core systems.
• Exposure to PHI reporting, data, or reconciliation processes
• Experience supporting cutover, deployment, or go-live activities
• Familiarity with common BA tooling (JIRA, Confluence, Visio, etc.)


Key Attributes
• Solid understanding of PHI business processes and terminology
• Analytical and detail-oriented
• Comfortable working in regulated environments
• Collaborative and delivery-focused

About Us
Strategy Assist is a boutique consulting firm that helps organisations deliver meaningful transformation across ERP, HCM, payroll, CRM, and digital platforms. We partner with businesses from mid-size to enterprise, empowering them to unlock growth through technology and innovation.

As we continue to expand our focus on digital transformation, AI, and automation, we're seeking a hands on Senior Project Manager to lead complex, enterprise grade technology projects across multiple industries, including professional services, healthcare, aged care, not-for-profit, and corporate sectors.

About the Role
This is more than a delivery role, it's a leadership opportunity for someone who thrives on driving outcomes, managing multiple high impact projects simultaneously, and working closely with clients to deliver tangible results. You'll take full ownership of project delivery across business applications, data transformation, AI automation, and digital integration, balancing strategic oversight with hands on execution.

You'll engage with senior stakeholders to ensure alignment between business goals and technology outcomes, while also identifying opportunities to expand services and strengthen client relationships.

Key Responsibilities

Lead multiple concurrent transformation programs with end-to-end accountability from inception to transition to BAU.

Oversee project governance, resource planning, budgeting, and risk/issue management across business and technology domains.

Develop and maintain trusted client partnerships through proactive communication and solution-oriented engagement.

Identify opportunities for value creation and new project initiatives with existing and prospective clients.

Drive structured project delivery frameworks that ensure consistency, efficiency, and quality.

Partner with clients to shape technology roadmaps across ERP, CRM, payroll, workforce, and automation solutions.

Mentor and develop project teams, promoting collaboration, accountability, and continuous improvement.

Ensure process and data interoperability across systems and business functions.

About You
You are a dynamic, business-minded leader who thrives in fast-paced, multi-project environments. You bring strong delivery discipline, commercial acumen, and a genuine passion for building relationships that drive business transformation.

Essential Requirements

Minimum 7+ years' experience managing large-scale digital or enterprise transformation projects.

Demonstrated experience managing transformation projects with budgets of $500K or above.

Proven ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously across diverse clients and sectors.

Strong record of stakeholder engagement, influencing at senior levels, and driving client outcomes.

Deep expertise across ERP, HCM, CRM, or related business applications.

Specific experience with Workday, Microsoft Dynamics, SAP, or any other major ERP, HCM, or CRM platform.

Advanced skills in governance, budgeting, risk/issue management, and reporting.

Proficiency with Microsoft Project, PowerPoint, Excel, and the Microsoft Office Suite.

Excellent written and verbal communication, including formal reporting and executive presentations.

Bachelor's degree in Business, IT, or a related discipline (or equivalent experience).

Hold a recognised project management certification such as PMP, PRINCE2, or equivalent.

Desirable Skills

Experience applying organisational change management methodologies (e.g., Prosci/ADKAR).

Familiarity with AI, automation, or data transformation initiatives.

Strong mentoring and people leadership experience.

Why Join Strategy Assist

Lead strategic transformation projects across multiple industries.

Collaborate with a senior team shaping the future of digital and AI-enabled consulting.

Work in a flexible, hybrid environment that values initiative and ownership.

Join an agile consultancy where your ideas and leadership directly influence success.

Eligibility
Only candidates based in Sydney with Australian Permanent Residency or Citizenship will be considered.

How to Apply
If you're ready to deliver impact across multiple projects and industries while building strong client relationships, send your résumé and cover letter to recruitment@strategyassist.com.au.

Please note: due to the volume of candidates, only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

Alinta Energy is one of Australia’s biggest energy retailers, generators and developers with over 1.1 million customers. Australia’s energy system is undergoing the biggest transformation in its history and we’re right there with it. We’re investing in and developing large-scale renewables and storage projects as part of our ongoing effort to provide our customers with reliable, affordable and sustainable energy.

We understand that flexibility matters when considering your next role. Let us know your requirements, and we’ll carefully consider how we might accommodate them.

Ready to make a real impact?

Step into a key role within Alinta Energy’s Group FP&A function, where you’ll help shape group level financial insight and executive decision making. Reporting to the FP&A Manager, this role operates at a group wide level, consolidating financial performance, supporting forecasting and budgeting, and producing executive ready reporting. The position is offered as a maximum term contract for 18 months (parental leave cover) and plays an important role in maintaining continuity, accuracy, and confidence in financial reporting within a complex and fast paced environment. This is a highly visible role that combines strong financial governance, analytical depth, and clear financial storytelling.

Why you’ll love working here

At Alinta Energy, we’re taking real action to deliver reliable and sustainable energy for Australia — and that practical approach runs through everything we do. You’ll get clear direction, genuine flexibility, and the support you need to grow, all while working on projects that make a lasting difference. We’re big enough to create impact, but small enough that your ideas and effort will always be seen.

There are plenty of other great benefits of working for Alinta Energy, including flexible working, energy discounts, an Employee Assistance Program (EAP), a paid volunteer day each year, fully stocked kitchens, and lots more.

What you'll do

Deliver group level performance reporting (month-end, rolling forecast, board/executive packs) with clear variance analysis, risks, opportunities, and strong cash flow insights.
Support budgeting and forecasting timetables, partnering with finance teams and business partners to build accurate, forward-looking views.
Enhance financial models and Power BI dashboards, driving automation and consistent reporting in partnership with systems teams.
Respond to ad hoc analysis and executive queries, including owners and government.
Identify and lead process improvements across reporting and analytics to reduce manual effort and lift quality and speed.

Your experience

Proven experience as a Senior Analyst (FP&A/financial analysis) in a large or complex environment, producing executive-level insights.
Strong accounting foundation with a tertiary finance/accounting degree and CA/CPA (or equivalent).
Recent hands on with Oracle EPM (FCCS/PBCS), advanced Excel, and Power BI.
Exceptional written and verbal communication; able to translate complex data into clear narratives for senior stakeholders.
Proactive, analytical, and resilient, with the confidence to challenge assumptions, influence stakeholders, and meet hard deadlines.

Please note this role requires full working rights within Australia.

Like what you’re seeing?

If you like the sound of this, and you’ve got experience in a similar role, we’d love to talk to you. Come and discover better together with Alinta Energy.

The Senior Manager, Business Intelligence leads the SA Housing Trust's well-established enterprise business intelligence capability, with a strong focus on broader business engagement and overall responsibility for data governance, data warehousing, analytics, insights and geographic information systems (GIS).

The role
Reporting to the Director, Digital and Business Services (CIO), you will contribute directly to the delivery and continuous improvement of the Trust's data and insights capability.
The role exists to ensure that:

Data is governed, secure and of high quality
Insights are timely, accurate and decision-ready
Information services are accessible and fit for purpose
You will set direction, provide leadership and ensure delivery across core business intelligence functions, working closely with executive leaders, directors and senior managers across the Trust.
This role balances strategic leadership with practical delivery.

Key accountabilities
You will:

Develop and lead the Trust's business intelligence vision and strategy
Assist in the further development and adoption of data governance and data quality frameworks
Oversee data warehousing, reporting, analytics and GIS capabilities
Engage senior stakeholders to translate business needs into BI solutions
Drive continuous improvement across BI processes, practices and delivery
About you
You will bring:

Significant experience leading business intelligence or data analytics functions
The ability to operate between strategy, stakeholders and delivery, with strong consulting and engagement skills
Sound people leadership and a passion for leading and delivering continuous improvement
Strong knowledge of data governance, data warehousing and analytics
A practical leadership style suited to complex and regulated environments
A degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Business Technology, BI, or another relevant field will be highly regarded, as will postgraduate qualifications 
Experience in the public sector or similarly regulated organisations will also be well regarded.

About SA Housing Trust
SA Housing Trust is responsible for delivering housing services and programs across South Australia, working with government, community and service partners to support sustainable housing outcomes. The Trust operates across metropolitan and regional locations and manages a large and diverse service portfolio.
